          VP Debate Likely to Focus on Policy

          Mike Pence and Tim Kaine, who will face off in the vice-presidential debate Tuesday night, are household names in their respective states with roughly two decades in elected office. Observers say both candidates are well-versed in policy and have a track record of rattling debate opponents.
